         <abstract>
            <p>This tutorial paper presents practical methods for accurately evaluating irregular Coulomb wave functions. Rational approximations to $G_0(\eta, \rho)$ and $G'_0(\eta, \rho)$ are developed along line segments in the $(\eta, \rho)$ plane to provide useful initial values for the associated differential equation. These approximations, designed for IBM System 360 Fortran double precision, yield results to at least 13 significant decimal places.</p>
          </abstract>
